    Split continuous ages to age groups

    ages.Rd

    Split continuous ages to age groups

    ages(x, groups, char)

    Arguments

    x

    Array with numeric values of age

    groups

    Array with numeric values of lower boundaries of age groups

    char

    Logical. Should output array be numeric (FALSE) or character (Factor) array (TRUE)

    Value

    Array with classified ages

    Examples

    groups <- c(0,1,5,10,15,20, 24, 45, 85)
x <- sample(0:100, 101)
ages(x, groups, FALSE)
#>   [1] 24 20 45 45 45 24 45 45 45  1 20 45 45  1 45 45 24 85 45 85 24 45 24 45 85
#>  [26]  1 85 24 45  5 24 45  5 20  5 45 45 15 45 45 85 85  0  5 45 45 45 45 24 85
#>  [51] 45 24  5 24 45 45 15 24 85 10 24 45 85 85  1 85 45 45 45 85 45 24 45 24 85
#>  [76] 45 10 45 85 45 24 45 24 45 10 45 85 45 15 24 15 10 15 85 24 24 20 24 10 45
#> [101] 24
